name: TD Active U.S. High Yield Bond ETF
longDescription: The investment objective of TD Active U.S. High Yield Bond ETF (the Fund) is to seek to earn income Fund investing in, or gaining exposure to, high-yield bonds issued by companies in the United States. In seeking to achieve this objective, the Fund invests primarily in high-yield corporate bonds rated BB+ to B- by nationally rated credit agencies at the time of purchase and may hold other income-generating securities. The Fund uses a bottom-up, buy-andhold strategy emphasizing analysis of credit fundamentals of the largest issuers of U.S. high-yield bonds in the context of a global macroeconomic environment. The Fund seeks to hedge substantially all foreign currency exposure back to Canadian dollars.
